{"title": "Spinner in the Sun", "description": "Myrtle Reed may always be depended upon to write a story in which poetry, charm, tenderness and humor are combined into a clever and entertaining book. Her characters are delightful and she always displays a quaint humor of expression and a quiet feeling of pathos which give a touch of active realism to all her writings.<br />\nIn \"A Spinner in the Sun\" she tells an old-fashioned love story, of a veiled lady who lives in solitude and whose features her neighbors have never seen. There is a mystery at the heart of the book that throws over it the glamour of romance (Summary by Grosset & Dunlap publishers, 1913)", "duration": 28934, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2406", "name": "Myrtle Reed"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt24/spinner_sun_1212.jpg", "copyright_year": "1906", "genres": ["Romance", "Published 1900 onward"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Crln Yldz Ksr"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Anna Simon"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Margaret Espaillat"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - \"The Fire was Kind\"", "readers": [6610], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/spinner_sun_1110_librivox/spinnerinthesun_01_reed_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1037}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - Miss Mehitable", "readers": [6708], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/spinner_sun_1110_librivox/spinnerinthesun_02_reed_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1178}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - The Pearls", "readers": [6708], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/spinner_sun_1110_librivox/spinnerinthesun_03_reed_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1137}, {"section": 4, "title": "04 - \"From the Depths of his Love\"", "readers": [5538], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/spinner_sun_1110_librivox/spinnerinthesun_04_reed_64kb.mp3", "duration": 729}, {"section": 5, "title": "05 - Araminta", "readers": [5538],